pullRequest.body:
From sphere-eversion (not written by me).
This basically shows that subspaces of codimension at least two are ample sets (PRed in #11342).

---------

In sphere-eversion, the hypotheses was spelled as "2 \leq Module.rank E"; I have changed this to "1 < Module.rank E" to match the remaining file. (The latter seems to be used more in mathlib, but either is pretty rare.)

nodes.body: Rebased on master (sorry for the force-push; only the last commit is new since the last review comment).
Bumped heartbeats in `CondexpL1.lean`; I have no idea why my change pushed things over the edge.

Good point; I agree. I have removed these lemmas and moved `isPathConnected_compl_of_two_le_codim` to `Analysis.NormedSpace.Connected` as well. I am not convinced if `Submodule.connectedComponentIn_eq_self_of_two_le_codim` is carrying its weight now; I can certainly remove it now and reconsider in the dependent PRs.

Well spotted; addressed now.

I'm not sure it makes sense to keep these two lemmas: they were tools to prove the connectedness of the complement of a point in dimension > 1 in the previous version, but since we already have this (and in fact a stronger result) I don't really see their use now.
Do you really use `E`? Below it seems it's only a submodule.
Indeed! Removed this.
